Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1365
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: Noncode.
Synopsis: FSSA report on managed care organization contracts.
Requires the office of the secretary of family and social services to, not
later than March 1, 2026, provide a written report to the budget
committee with specified information concerning any termination of a
managed care organization's Medicaid contract in 2025.
Effective: January 1, 2026 (retroactive).
Porter
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
2026 IN 1365—LS 6360/DI 104

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1365
A BILL FOR AN ACT concerning human services.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. [EFFECTIVE JANUARY 1, 2026 (RETROACTIVE)]
2 (a) As used in this SECTION, "budget committee" refers to the
3 budget committee established by IC 4-12-1-3(b).
4 (b) As used in this SECTION, "office of the secretary" refers to
5 the office of the secretary of family and social services established
6 by IC 12-8-1.5-1.
7 (c) Not later than March 1, 2026, the office of the secretary shall
8 submit a written report to the budget committee that includes all
9 information relating to the cost, analysis, reasoning, and decision
10 for the termination of any Medicaid contract with a managed care
11 organization that served at least two hundred thousand (200,000)
12 Medicaid recipients during the 2025 calendar year. The report
13 must include the following supporting documentation:
14 (1) Any electronic mail, including internal and external mail,
15 related to the analysis and decision to terminate a contract.
16 (2) Any memoranda related to the analysis and decision to
17 terminate a contract.
18 (3) Any performance related data concerning the managed
2026 IN 1365—LS 6360/DI 104

2
1 care organization's contract.
2 (4) Any cost related analysis of services provided under the
3 contract and costs related to the termination of the contract.
4 (d) This SECTION expires December 31, 2026.
5 SECTION 2. An emergency is declared for this act.
